tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal cells showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining which often was combined with nuclear positivity. Placenta, thyroid gland and the intestines expressed strong staining. Glial cells and reaction center cells in lymphoid tissues were negative.

subcellularLocation.summary: Localized to the nucleus but excluded from the nucleoli.

tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal cells showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining which often was combined with nuclear positivity. Placenta, thyroid gland and the intestines expressed strong staining. Glial cells and reaction center cells in lymphoid tissues were negative.

The majority of malignant cells were either negative or displayed weak cytoplasmic and/or nuclear immunoreactivity. Many tumor types showed moderate staining in occasional cases e.g. testicular and pancreatic cancers.
